notes.noteText: Menu submitted for RD approval

Hello Mynor, I will be using the Program & Nutrition Standards Checklist to review your menu (go to Media Library and search for "standards checklist" to view them all by station). I will leave comments here for anything that needs to be addressed. If there's a reason your program is different, please ask your DM to update the new exceptions tool in our system so we know exactly what to look for and what not to look for, too. There are currently no exceptions listed.

Menu Length:
Due to the new Menu Builder launch coming soon, we are allowing for longer Fall menus to give you more time to prepare Winter menus. This menu should run up until your Winter Break in December. Please let me know what this date is and I will extend your menu for you.

Accurate Recipe Titles:
It looks like the title of an item has been changed and that title no longer accurately reflects the recipe. This is a problem because online ingredients and allergen information won't make sense to our customers. You can see the original title by hovering over it with your cursor, or click on the cell, then click the magnifying glass next to the item to see a preview of the recipe. Please adjust the following titles: Eggplant & Feta Cheese Sandwiches (week 1 Thurs), Turkey & Bean Rice Soup (week 2 Mon), Farro Mediterranean Salad (week 2 Mon), Israeli Couscous with Tomatoes (week 2 Mon), Vegetable Burgers with Basil Mayo (week 3 Tues), Apple & Cheddar Sandwich (week 3 Thurs), Sauteed Collard Greens & Mushrooms (week 3 Fri), Quinoa Salad with Carrots & Raisins (week 3 Fri), Shrimp Primavera (week 4 Tues – add “pasta” back to title), Lemon Hummus (week 4 Wed)

Consistent Recipe IDs:
Recipe IDs for items with the same title must match to prevent the wrong recipe from being made/served and potentially causing an allergic reaction. Items with multiple recipe IDs are: Cream of Broccoli Soup, Corn & Tomato Salad, Pasta Salad, Tabbouleh, Lemon Hummus, Baked Potato Wedges, House-Made Alfredo Sauce, Pasta Bar. Please find them on the menu by hitting ctrl + f and typing in the item you are looking for. Go through each unique week to find the items on the menu. Make it so all the same menu items link to the recipe you will be making.

Community allergies considered:
Based on the food allergy survey from last year, the allergies in your community from the top 12 (besides peanuts & tree nuts) are: shellfish (25 students), sesame (15), soy (11), fish (9), milk (7), wheat (5), gluten (5). Your menu has options for these allergies, good job! Do you offer gluten-free bread for sandwiches? If so, please list on the Daily menu. 

FYI – there are several sesame-free recipes for hummus in the Database. This would be great to have all sesame-free hummus since you have a decent number of sesame allergies. 

Please send us an updated list when you receive it from the school.

Stock Exchange:
•	When offering 2 soups/day, one should be vegetarian. Please adjust: week 1 Wed

Classic Cuts:
•	We have been asked to take a closer look at deli salads. They should be protein based (that could be served on bread, like chicken salad, egg salad or shrimp salad) or make sense at a deli (think potato salads, pasta salads and slaws). On your menu the “Cauliflower Salad (week 2 Fri), Balsamic Vegetable Salad (week 3 Fri)” don’t quite fit the bill. Can you swap these out for something else?

Main Ingredient:
•	I see you serve more than 1 entree. One entree should be vegetarian. Please add to: week 1 Thurs, week 2 Wed, week 4 Tues (these dishes are vegetable sides, not entrees). 
•	We always need to offer at least 1 green/yellow dot entree every day. Please adjust: week 1 Tues, week 2 Fri.

Vegetable standards:
•	The standard is to have 2 vegetables daily, including a steamed/plain (salt & pepper only) and a green-colored vegetable. These can be one and the same (for example: steamed broccoli meets both criteria). 
•	Need a steamed/plain vegetable on: week 2 Tues, week 3 Thurs

Paquitos:
Need beans on week 3 Wed & Thurs and week 4 Wed (green beans aren’t the traditional type of bean served in Latin countries with rice).
Don't forget, once your menu is approved, you'll need to reprint all recipes since they may have been updated (including updates to allergen tagging).

Please scroll up to view all the comments. Address them by either updating the menu or having your DM update the SAGE Program Exceptions in the Client Management tool. Thanks for all your hard work on this menu! We appreciate all you do to make our SAGE menus great.
Menu returned by RD/DM for corrections
Thank you Sarah, all the corrections are done.
Menu submitted for RD approval
HI there, thanks for the changes. I still see 2 different recipes for Baked Potato Wedges and House-Made Alfredo Sauce.
Do you offer gluten-free bread?
Still need a vegetarian entree at Main Ingred on week 4 Tues.
Still have 2 red dot entrees on week 1 Tues and week 2 Fri.
The beans you added on week 3 Wed are not from Cuba, please replace. You also still need a bean on week 3 Thurs.
Please address these comments and resubmit.
Menu returned by RD/DM for corrections

Sarah,
we serve GF Breads from Udi's. I don't see any choices for GF breads.
Just Home made GF bread options.
Menu submitted for RD approval
Hi Mynor, I'll be checking your menu for the changes made for Sarah since she is out today. Looks like the recipe IDs and vegetarian entree look good now.
I would like to see another authentic bean added for Thurs wk 3- there are several for Mexico as options.

In the recipe database there should be Gluten-Free White Bread and Gluten-Free Hamburger Bun that would be good options to menu on your Daily Menu for those customers who would need that options (depending up what type of Udi's product you are purchasing, sliced bread or rolls). Let me know if you have any questions. Thank you so much for all of your hard work! Best, Melissa
Menu returned by RD/DM for corrections
Menu submitted for RD approval
Good news! Your menu is approved and I will send it on to your DM for a final look. Please don’t forget to reprint all recipes once your DM approves. Have a great fall!
Menu approved by RD. Menu submitted for DM approval

Hi Mynor, real quick we do need you menu to run up to your Winter break with the new Menu Builder launching this fall. I would hate for your menu to expire during the transition time. Please extend your menu- thanks!
Menu approved by DM!
